---

<section id="faq" class="faq-section">
  <div class="container">
    <div class="section-header">
      <h2>Frequently Asked Questions</h2>
      <p>Everything you need to know about ContentFlow</p>
    </div>

    <div class="faq-grid">
      <div class="faq-item">
        <button class="faq-question">
          <span>Does the AI really sound like me?</span>
          <span class="icon">+</span>
        </button>
        <div class="faq-answer">
          <p>Yes. The Psychology Engine learns your voice through weekly rituals and evolves with your narrative arc. It's not generic AI — it's trained on your specific positioning, tone, and audience personas.</p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="faq-item">
        <button class="faq-question">
          <span>What content formats are supported?</span>
          <span class="icon">+</span>
        </button>
        <div class="faq-answer">
          <p>Blog articles, newsletters, social posts (Twitter/LinkedIn/Instagram), short-form video scripts (TikTok/Reels/Shorts), and YouTube video scripts. One idea generates all formats.</p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="faq-item">
        <button class="faq-question">
          <span>Where can I publish from ContentFlow?</span>
          <span class="icon">+</span>
        </button>
        <div class="faq-answer">
          <p>Twitter/X, LinkedIn, Instagram, TikTok, YouTube, Ghost, and WordPress. Connect your accounts via OAuth in the Settings screen. More platforms coming soon.</p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="faq-item">
        <button class="faq-question">
          <span>Do I review every piece of content?</span>
          <span class="icon">+</span>
        </button>
        <div class="faq-answer">
          <p>Yes, you're always in control. AI generates, you approve. The swipe feed makes review fast — most creators spend 5-10 minutes reviewing a day's worth of content.</p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="faq-item">
        <button class="faq-question">
          <span>How does SEO work?</span>
          <span class="icon">+</span>
        </button>
        <div class="faq-answer">
          <p>ContentFlow uses DataForSEO for real keyword data, competitor analysis, and SERP tracking. Articles are optimized for keywords with real search volume. Your content ranks because it's data-driven, not guessed.</p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="faq-item">
        <button class="faq-question">
          <span>What about affiliate links?</span>
          <span class="icon">+</span>
        </button>
        <div class="faq-answer">
          <p>Register your affiliate programs with keywords. AI automatically weaves relevant links into generated content when the topic matches. You control which programs are active.</p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="faq-item">
        <button class="faq-question">
          <span>Are API costs included?</span>
          <span class="icon">+</span>
        </button>
        <div class="faq-answer">
          <p>Yes. All AI generation costs (LLM, search, analysis) are included in your plan. No surprise bills. The pricing is what you see.</p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="faq-item">
        <button class="faq-question">
          <span>Can I use it on mobile?</span>
          <span class="icon">+</span>
        </button>
        <div class="faq-answer">
          <p>The Flutter app works on Android, iOS, and web. Review and approve content from anywhere. The swipe interface was designed mobile-first.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<style>
  .faq-section {
    padding: 6rem 0;
    background: var(--color-light-gray);
  }

  .container {
    max-width: 900px;
    margin: 0 auto;
    padding: 0 2rem;
  }

  .section-header {
    text-align: center;
    margin-bottom: 4rem;
  }

  .section-header h2 {
    font-size: 3rem;
    margin-bottom: 1rem;
    color: var(--color-dark);
  }

  .section-header p {
    font-size: 1.25rem;
    color: var(--color-gray);
  }

  .faq-grid {
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    gap: 1rem;
  }

  .faq-item {
    background: white;
    border-radius: 12px;
    overflow: hidden;
    transition: all 0.3s ease;
  }

  .faq-item:hover {
    box-shadow: 0 4px 20px rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.08);
  }

  .faq-question {
    width: 100%;
    padding: 1.5rem;
    display: flex;
    justify-content: space-between;
    align-items: center;
    text-align: left;
    font-size: 1.1rem;
    font-weight: 600;
    color: var(--color-dark);
    cursor: pointer;
    transition: all 0.3s ease;
  }

  .faq-question:hover {
    color: var(--color-primary);
  }

  .icon {
    font-size: 1.5rem;
    font-weight: 300;
    transition: transform 0.3s ease;
  }

  .faq-item.active .icon {
    transform: rotate(45deg);
  }

  .faq-answer {
    max-height: 0;
    overflow: hidden;
    transition: max-height 0.3s ease, padding 0.3s ease;
  }

  .faq-item.active .faq-answer {
    max-height: 500px;
    padding: 0 1.5rem 1.5rem;
  }

  .faq-answer p {
    color: var(--color-gray);
    line-height: 1.7;
  }

  @media (max-width: 768px) {
    .section-header h2 {
      font-size: 2rem;
    }

    .faq-question {
      font-size: 1rem;
    }
  }
</style>

<script>
  const faqItems = document.querySelectorAll('.faq-item');
  
  faqItems.forEach(item => {
    const question = item.querySelector('.faq-question');
    
    question?.addEventListener('click', () => {
      const isActive = item.classList.contains('active');
      
      // Close all items
      faqItems.forEach(i => i.classList.remove('active'));
      
      // Open clicked item if it wasn't active
      if (!isActive) {
        item.classList.add('active');
      }
    });
  });
</script>
